SHORT

  Hollywood mode for Cubic IDE

AUTHOR

  Michael Jurisch (plug-in and icons ©Dietmar Eilert and used with permission)

DESCRIPTION

  Adds Hollywood mode to Cubic IDE (installs a new filetype)

INSTALLATION

  Doubleclick at the installer script icon.

USAGE

  Simply load a Hollywood script (file name suffix *.hws): the
  editor will immediately switch to the Hollywood editing environment.
  The command SET TYPE=".hws" starts the Hollywood environment, too.

  For more information please open the manual under manual/hw4cubic.html.

CONTACT

  Please post bug reports, comments and suggestions to the official Hollywood
  forums at http://forums.hollywood-mal.com/
  
  Please send Pay Pal donations to radcliffe@gmx.de :-)

